# Model Update Skill

This runbook documents the full process for safely discovering new LLM models and adding them to the SDK. Every step should be completed in order. LLMs hallucinate model names â€” do not skip the verification steps.

---

## 1. UNDERSTAND THE CODEBASE FIRST

Read these files before making any changes:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `spaik_sdk/models/model_registry.py` | **Primary file**: all model definitions and aliases |
| `spaik_sdk/models/llm_model.py` | `LLMModel` dataclass â€” understand all fields |
| `spaik_sdk/models/llm_config.py` | `LLMConfig` â€” per-request params, NOT per-model |
| `spaik_sdk/models/llm_families.py` | Family constants (used in `LLMModel.family`) |
| `spaik_sdk/models/providers/azure_provider.py` | Azure deployment env var map â€” must stay in sync |
| `spaik_sdk/llm/cost/builtin_cost_provider.py` | Pricing per model in USD cents/MTok |
| `spaik_sdk/models/factories/anthropic_factory.py` | Anthropic-specific config (thinking, budget_tokens) |
| `spaik_sdk/models/factories/openai_factory.py` | OpenAI-specific config (reasoning effort, summary, responses API) |
| `spaik_sdk/models/factories/google_factory.py` | Google-specific config (thinking_budget, include_thoughts) |
| `spaik_sdk/models/providers/provider_type.py` | Provider enum + `from_model_name` logic (update if needed) |
| `spaik_sdk/attachments/provider_support.py` | Per-family attachment MIME type support |

