## 7. POST-CHANGE CHECKLIST

After making changes, run in `packages/agent-sdk/`:

```bash
make lint-fix && make typecheck && make test-unit
```

Manually verify:
- [ ] New model can be looked up by `ModelRegistry.from_name("alias")`
- [ ] Azure env var name follows `AZURE_<MODEL>_DEPLOYMENT` pattern
- [ ] Cost provider handles the new model name (test `from_name` with the exact ID)
- [ ] No duplicate model IDs in the registry

---

## 8. REPORT TO USER

After completing an update pass, always report:
1. **New models added**: name, API ID, reasoning support, pricing
2. **Models found deprecated/retiring**: warn user
3. **Models with uncertain IDs**: list with concern
4. **Models not yet in API**: note that they exist but were not added

